<title>The treatment of the &apos;growing&apos; girl </title>
<summary>||kabbo describes the seclusion of the &apos;growing&apos; (or menstruating) girl in a hut with a tiny door by her mother: she has to lookeep her eyes on the ground when she leaves the hut and cannot go far. When she is &apos;grown&apos; she is allowed to look about and leave the hut and walk about like other women.</summary><comments>1) See <i>The girl who made the Milky Way, by throwing ashes into the sky</i>, 2) This story is found in Book II-28</comments><date>January or February 1873</date><storypages>2520v &amp; 2521v </storypages><category>New maidens</category><category>Custom and daily life</category><author>||kabbo (Jantje) (II)</author><keyword><kw>seclusion</kw><subkw>the treatment of the &apos;growing&apos; girl</subkw></keyword>
